

---
const pageTitle = "Tree of Life";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0 8px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(6deg);
        width: 320px;
        height: 320px;
        opacity: 0.28;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        display: block;
        filter: contrast(1.1);
        opacity: 1;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 40px;
        line-height: 1.05;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 16px;
        margin: 0 0 24px;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }

      p { margin: 0 0 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px 16px;
        background: var(--soft);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 34px 0 16px;
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
        font-size: 16px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 4px 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        html, body { font-size: 17px; }
        h1 { font-size: 32px; }
        .frame { padding: 18px 16px 24px; }
        .symbol-bg {
          width: 220px;
          height: 220px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">symbols index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/symbols/serpent">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/symbols/mandala">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none">
            <g stroke="#000000" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="150" cy="42" r="16" />
              <circle cx="104" cy="82" r="16" />
              <circle cx="196" cy="82" r="16" />
              <circle cx="150" cy="122" r="16" />
              <circle cx="104" cy="162" r="16" />
              <circle cx="196" cy="162" r="16" />
              <circle cx="150" cy="202" r="16" />
              <circle cx="150" cy="248" r="16" />

              <path d="M150 58 L150 106" />
              <path d="M150 58 L104 66" />
              <path d="M150 58 L196 66" />
              <path d="M104 98 L150 106" />
              <path d="M196 98 L150 106" />
              <path d="M104 98 L104 146" />
              <path d="M196 98 L196 146" />
              <path d="M150 138 L104 146" />
              <path d="M150 138 L196 146" />
              <path d="M104 178 L150 186" />
              <path d="M196 178 L150 186" />
              <path d="M150 218 L150 232" />

              <path d="M150 20
                       C182 20, 215 36, 232 64
                       C248 90, 242 120, 220 142
                       C206 156, 202 174, 206 190
                       C212 214, 230 228, 250 236" />
              <path d="M150 20
                       C118 20, 85 36, 68 64
                       C52 90, 58 120, 80 142
                       C94 156, 98 174, 94 190
                       C88 214, 70 228, 50 236" />
              <path d="M150 218
                       C138 238, 126 252, 110 266" />
              <path d="M150 218
                       C162 238, 174 252, 190 266" />
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Tree of Life</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">symbols / structure / growth / archive entry 004</p>

          <div class="divider">***</div>

          <p>
            The tree of life appears across cultures as an image of connection.
            Roots descend into darkness, branches reach toward light, and the trunk
            holds the tension between below and above. It is a living axis.
          </p>

          <p>
            Because of this, the tree often represents the structure of being itself.
            It shows how different levels of existence remain linked rather than
            separate. What grows above depends on what is rooted below.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            what reaches upward is sustained by what is hidden beneath.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">roots and branches</h2>

          <p>
            Psychologically, the roots can be seen as the unconscious, memory,
            instinct, and ancestry. The branches represent conscious life, thought,
            action, and outward expression.
          </p>

          <p>
            Growth does not come from ignoring one side, but from maintaining the
            connection between them. When roots are denied, the visible structure
            weakens. When branches are suppressed, life loses expression.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">center and axis</h2>

          <p>
            Many traditions treat the tree as a center point, a place where worlds
            meet. It becomes a symbol of alignment, where different layers of life
            are brought into relation rather than fragmentation.
          </p>

          <p>
            In this sense, the tree of life is not static. It is always growing,
            always changing, but it maintains a coherent structure while doing so.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">back to symbols index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/mandala">continue to: mandala</a>
            <a class="red" href="/symbols/serpent">serpent</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">
            this page is part of the hidden archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>